thread.title: The 10-Point.

author: Gerard Baker
title: The 10-Point.
text:
Good morning,
The Rising Road
Federal Reserve officials signaled growing confidence in the U.S. economy when they met in January, bolstering plans to continue raising short-term interest rates this year. Several Fed officials believed the economy was set to grow even faster than when they elevated growth projections at their December session, according to minutes from the latest policy gathering.
